    <div class="blog-post">
        <h2 class="blog-post-title">The problem that we are tackling</h2>
        <p class="blog-post-meta">Why is this an important problem to solve? Why is this a tough problem? Why hasn't it been solved before?</p>
        <hr>
        <p>Artificial gene (AG) is a DNA molecule, synthesized <i>de novo</i> by a complex of chemical, physical and enzymatic methods. Nowadays AGs have found application in gene therapy of hereditary disorders, protein engineering, biopharmaceutics, metabolic engineering, diagnostics, information storage (NAM –Nucleic Acid Memory), artificial life etc. Artificial gene synthesis is a key step in biotechnology R&D. The price for gene synthesis remains high enough (0.2 $ per base pair), because of complexity of the process. The problem of high cost for gene synthesis hasn’t been solved yet for two main reasons: the requirements for AG were low 5 more years ago, so manual gene synthesis was enough, but market is growing very fast now; main DNA-related-equipment-producing companies last years were focused on new generation sequencing methods and did not invest in gene synthesis equipment and methods.</p>
    </div><!-- /.blog-post -->

    <div class="blog-post">
        <h2 class="blog-post-title">Our solution</h2>
        <p class="blog-post-meta">Why is this a unique or different approach? What positive impact will this project have at scale?</p>

        <p>Our solution is a cheap “black-box”-type equipment (&lt25 000 $) that is able to synthesize gene from idea to test-tube for extremely low price (&lt0.05 $ per base pair). All current solutions for automated gene synthesis are robotic-based extensive and very expensive equipment that aimed at replacing human labor with machine. Our solution is based on combination of oligonucleotide synthesizer and high-throughput gene assembly module.  System is controlled by cloud-based software platform (Web of Scientific Equipment) that is able to make intellectual decisions even in case of “difficult” genes. In the future we planning to develop system in direction of microfluidic devices in order to make gene synthesis cheaper. Realization of this project can lower price for gene synthesis, that makes AGs to be much cheaper than gene cloning so this will promote development of gene therapy and biotechnology.</p>

    </div><!-- /.blog-post -->

    <div class="blog-post">
        <h2 class="blog-post-title">The technical insight</h2>
        <p class="blog-post-meta">What is the breakthrough science or tech that makes our project possible? Why is our team excited to work on this?</p>

        <p>We have already started working on gene synthesizer based on the flow-through PCR thermocycler. Our “know-how” is the high-throughput polymerase chain reaction-gene assembly module and high-performance cloud computing optimization strategies. Control system includes web application(ASP.NET MVC) and cross-platform mobile application(Xamarin.Forms) with offline synchronization to prevent any connection issues. The best part of our system is how to easy it is to use. Customer simply specify the original sequence and kick off optimization and synthesizing processes in the cloud. Our team has 10-years of experience in the protein engineering and software development areas. We are having a passion to change the world by reducing price of AG synthesizing which is revolutionizing biotechnology research and we are planning to build own gene synthesis facility. So that’s why our team so excited to work on this project.</p>

    </div><!-- /.blog-post -->

